  `Clock.Real`) **or** a registered process name for a `Clock.Fake` server
  (like `:my_test_clock`). Distinguish the two using
  `function_exported?/3`: if `clock` exports a `now/0` function, call
  `clock.now()` directly (the module-atom case); otherwise treat the atom as a
  registered name and forward it to `Clock.Fake.now/1`.
- When `clock` is anything else (e.g. a PID), forward it directly to
